# Image Optimization Rules

Every time we generate or add new images to this project, ALWAYS perform these steps:

## 1. Resize
- Max width: **1280px**
- Use `sips --resampleWidth 1280` on macOS

## 2. Convert to WebP
- Use `cwebp -q 82 -m 6` to convert to WebP format
- Quality 82 is the sweet spot for this project (good quality, small size)

## 3. Remove originals
- After successful WebP conversion, delete the original JPG/PNG files
- Only keep `.webp` files in `public/images/`

## 4. Reference with .webp extension
- All image paths in code (articles.ts, components, etc.) must use `.webp` extension
- Never reference `.jpg` or `.png` for article/generated images

## 5. Cache headers
- The project has a custom `Caddyfile` with 1-year immutable cache for static assets
- No extra action needed — just make sure files go to `public/images/`

## Quick one-liner for batch conversion
```bash
for f in *.jpg *.png; do
  [ -f "$f" ] || continue
  BASE="${f%.*}"
  sips --resampleWidth 1280 "$f" --out "/tmp/resized_$f"
  cwebp -q 82 -m 6 "/tmp/resized_$f" -o "${BASE}.webp"
  rm "$f"
done
```

## Size targets
- Cover images: 80-180 KB (webp)
- Interior/article images: 30-240 KB (webp)
- If any image exceeds 300 KB — reduce quality to 75 or resize to 1024px width
